Look, I know the TSA

01:16.310 --> 01:17.478
Look, I know the TSA

01:17.478 --> 01:19.079
screenings are annoying, but

01:19.079 --> 01:20.080
they stop terrorists.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.649
Actually, there's very little

01:21.649 --> 01:23.517
evidence that the TSA has ever

01:23.517 --> 01:25.319
stopped a terrorist, let alone

01:25.319 --> 01:26.187
one with a bomb.

01:26.187 --> 01:28.021
Hey!

01:28.021 --> 01:30.158
Don't say "bomb."

01:30.158 --> 01:30.991
Wait, wait, wait.

01:30.991 --> 01:32.693
Haven't they stopped an attack?

01:32.693 --> 01:33.694
Not that we know of.

01:33.694 --> 01:34.428
They didn't stop the shoe

01:34.428 --> 01:35.095
bomber.

01:35.095 --> 01:35.863
They didn't stop the underwear

01:35.863 --> 01:36.530
bomber.

01:36.530 --> 01:37.465
Heck, they probably won't stop

01:37.465 --> 01:38.132
the crop top bomber.

01:38.132 --> 01:41.302
(ticking, alarm ringing)

01:41.302 --> 01:42.136
So what did stop all those

01:42.136 --> 01:42.803
bombs?

01:42.803 --> 01:43.537
Oh, easy.

01:43.537 --> 01:45.139
All the other security measures

01:45.139 --> 01:46.507
we added since 9/11.

01:46.507 --> 01:48.276
Like reinforced cockpit blast

01:48.276 --> 01:49.042
doors.

01:49.042 --> 01:49.877
The increased number of

01:49.877 --> 01:50.944
air marshals.

01:50.944 --> 01:52.045
The heightened awareness of

01:52.045 --> 01:53.381
passengers like you and me.

01:53.381 --> 01:55.015
And intelligence agencies that

01:55.015 --> 01:56.550
work to stop attacks before they

01:56.550 --> 01:57.485
even happen.

01:57.485 --> 01:59.052
Yeah, we knew about this guy.

01:59.052 --> 02:01.155
We replaced his bullets with

02:01.155 --> 02:02.623
Tic-Tacs.

02:02.623 --> 02:04.458
Mm, orange.

02:04.458 --> 02:05.959
My favorite.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.828
But the TSA does nothing.

02:07.828 --> 02:09.297
For one thing, they straight up

02:09.297 --> 02:10.664
suck at screening.

02:10.664 --> 02:11.899
When the Department of Homeland

02:11.899 --> 02:13.734
Security tested them, the TSA

02:13.734 --> 02:15.203
failed to find mock weapons

02:15.203 --> 02:18.306
and explosives 95% of the time.

02:18.306 --> 02:20.174
No way, really?

02:20.174 --> 02:21.509
Hey!

02:21.509 --> 02:24.378
You can't bring this knife here.

02:24.378 --> 02:26.013
Here are your other knives back.

02:26.013 --> 02:27.381
Also, if you wouldn't mind, real

02:27.381 --> 02:28.716
big smile, pose for Instagram.

02:28.716 --> 02:29.383
(camera clicking)

02:29.383 --> 02:30.050
Beautiful.

02:30.050 --> 02:30.718
Instagram?

02:30.718 --> 02:31.819
Yeah, they post everything

02:31.819 --> 02:33.086
they confiscate to Instagram,

02:33.086 --> 02:35.356
and it's pretty embarrassing.

02:35.356 --> 02:36.089
What filter do you like?

02:36.089 --> 02:37.725
Do you like Kelvin?

02:37.725 --> 02:38.392
Mayfair.

02:38.392 --> 02:39.059
Oh.

02:39.059 --> 02:39.727
All day.

02:39.727 --> 02:40.394
All right.

02:40.394 --> 02:41.061
Most of the stuff they

02:41.061 --> 02:42.696
confiscate is just novelty crap.

02:42.696 --> 02:43.931
No, look, that's a grenade.

02:43.931 --> 02:45.266
No, that's just a vape that's

02:45.266 --> 02:46.334
shaped like a grenade.

02:46.334 --> 02:47.568
How is that dangerous?

02:47.568 --> 02:49.237
That's a samurai sword.

02:49.237 --> 02:49.937
That's a weapon.

02:49.937 --> 02:50.838
No, those aren't weapons.

02:50.838 --> 02:52.406
Those are replica weapons.

02:52.406 --> 02:53.674
And their owner isn't a

02:53.674 --> 02:55.676
terrorist, he's a dweeb.

02:55.676 --> 02:57.177
And stop calling them samurai

02:57.177 --> 02:57.845
swords.

02:57.845 --> 02:59.680
It's a Master Sword replica from

02:59.680 --> 03:00.948
"The Legend of Zelda,"

03:00.948 --> 03:01.615
all right?

03:01.615 --> 03:03.183
Confiscating fake weapons and

03:03.183 --> 03:05.052
stopping people from just saying

03:05.052 --> 03:05.786
the word "bomb"--

03:05.786 --> 03:06.920
Don't say "bomb"!

03:06.920 --> 03:07.588
(sighs)

03:07.588 --> 03:08.689
Come on, man.

03:08.689 --> 03:09.357
Get up.

03:09.357 --> 03:10.791
Those things do nothing to

03:10.791 --> 03:12.092
stop terrorism.

03:12.092 --> 03:13.727
They just create the illusion

03:13.727 --> 03:14.595
of security.

03:14.595 --> 03:16.464
It's a concept called security

03:16.464 --> 03:17.431
theater.

03:17.431 --> 03:18.899
Good morrow, sir.

03:18.899 --> 03:21.034
Now, won't you step aside?

03:21.034 --> 03:23.304
For I perceive the mace your

03:23.304 --> 03:24.438
breeches hide.

03:24.438 --> 03:25.273
(crowd exclaiming)

03:25.273 --> 03:27.375
Alas to wastrel villains such

03:27.375 --> 03:30.110
as I, who ne'er shall breach thy

03:30.110 --> 03:31.812
fine "securit-eye."

03:31.812 --> 03:34.815
(applause)

03:34.815 --> 03:36.750
I feel so safe!

03:36.750 --> 03:38.319
Security theater is a show

03:38.319 --> 03:39.920
the agency puts on to make it

03:39.920 --> 03:40.821
look like they're doing a lot

03:40.821 --> 03:42.923
to protect us...

03:42.923 --> 03:44.825
Found another grenade vape!

03:44.825 --> 03:45.493
(camera clicking)

03:45.493 --> 03:47.160
And make sure to tag me, David.

03:47.160 --> 03:48.095
Even though they're not.

03:48.095 --> 03:48.762
What?

03:48.762 --> 03:49.463
Who's that?

03:49.463 --> 03:50.731
I was hoping you'd show up.

03:50.731 --> 03:51.799
That's Bruce Schneier.

03:51.799 --> 03:52.900
He's a renowned expert on

03:52.900 --> 03:53.734
security theater.

03:53.767 --> 03:55.168
Why is he a scooter?

03:55.168 --> 03:55.903
I'm broadcasting from a

03:55.936 --> 03:57.137
secure location.

03:57.137 --> 03:58.005
And I couldn't get through the

03:58.005 --> 03:58.839
metal detector.

03:58.839 --> 04:00.474
Anyway, as far as screening

04:00.474 --> 04:02.142
goes, what we had before

04:02.142 --> 04:03.511
September 11th is actually quite

04:03.511 --> 04:04.345
adequate.

04:04.345 --> 04:05.646
Taking your shoes off and

04:05.646 --> 04:06.647
putting your liquids in a

04:06.647 --> 04:08.181
separate bag doesn't actually

04:08.181 --> 04:09.082
make you safer.

04:09.082 --> 04:10.284
It just makes you feel safer.

04:10.284 --> 04:11.919
But if we feel safer, isn't

04:11.919 --> 04:13.020
that-- isn't that good?

04:13.020 --> 04:14.121
Well, first, the illusion of

04:14.121 --> 04:15.489
security isn't worth it if you

04:15.489 --> 04:16.524
have to give up essential

04:16.524 --> 04:17.691
freedoms and privacies

04:17.691 --> 04:18.359
to get it.

04:18.359 --> 04:19.026
Ooh!

04:19.026 --> 04:19.760
Hey, watch it!

04:19.760 --> 04:21.094
Stop clenching.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.463
And secondly, it's dangerous

04:22.463 --> 04:23.531
to present the illusion of

04:23.531 --> 04:24.965
security when the system is

04:24.965 --> 04:25.799
actually quite vulnerable to

04:25.799 --> 04:26.467
terrorist attacks.

04:26.467 --> 04:27.134
What?

04:27.134 --> 04:27.801
It is?

04:27.801 --> 04:28.869
Oh, yeah, even if this

04:28.869 --> 04:29.937
screening worked, it would only

04:29.937 --> 04:31.372
protect us against the last way

04:31.372 --> 04:32.272
we were attacked.

04:32.272 --> 04:32.940
It does nothing to stop

04:32.940 --> 04:33.941
terrorists from finding new ways

04:33.941 --> 04:35.676
to hurt us.

04:35.676 --> 04:36.844
The terrorists can see our

04:36.844 --> 04:37.711
security.

04:37.711 --> 04:38.979
They can figure out how to get

04:38.979 --> 04:39.713
around it.

04:39.713 --> 04:40.548
So instead of trying to make

04:40.548 --> 04:42.149
airports impregnable, we should

04:42.149 --> 04:43.216
take the money we're wasting on

04:43.216 --> 04:45.052
the TSA and spend it on things

04:45.052 --> 04:46.487
that work-- intelligence,

04:46.487 --> 04:48.121
investigation, and emergency

04:48.121 --> 04:48.889
response.

04:48.889 --> 04:49.823
Face it, Phil.

04:49.823 --> 04:51.625
The TSA does nothing but violate

04:51.625 --> 04:53.561
your privacy and waste your

04:53.561 --> 04:54.462
time.

04:54.462 --> 04:57.898
Man, this robot is right.

04:57.898 --> 04:59.500
I quit.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.402
Oh, these uniforms are very

05:01.402 --> 05:02.069
cheap.

05:02.069 --> 05:03.804
You're free to go.

05:03.804 --> 05:05.406
Now I missed my flight.

05:05.406 --> 05:06.073
Are you happy?

05:06.073 --> 05:07.307
I have a migraine.

05:07.307 --> 05:08.676
I'll get you home.

05:08.676 --> 05:10.143
(energy crackling)

05:10.143 --> 05:11.979
Whoa.

05:11.979 --> 05:13.246
I can't get the Tylenol open.

05:13.246 --> 05:14.382
Oh, yeah, funny story about

05:14.382 --> 05:15.583
those tamper-resistant seals.

05:15.583 --> 05:16.850
More security theater.

05:16.850 --> 05:18.085
Here, I'll show you on the way.

05:18.085 --> 05:19.687
No!

05:19.687 --> 05:21.389
(energy ringing)

05:26.594 --> 05:27.728
Hey, this thing is my private

05:27.728 --> 05:28.396
property.

05:28.396 --> 05:29.430
Nope, now we're gonna hang

05:29.430 --> 05:31.164
out and be best friends.

05:31.164 --> 05:32.600
♪♪

