So, virtually every pill

05:57.858 --> 05:59.126
bottle in here has a

05:59.126 --> 06:00.861
"tamper-resistant seal."

06:00.861 --> 06:01.529
Why do you think that is?

06:01.529 --> 06:02.195
I don't know.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.296
I guess people tamper with

06:03.296 --> 06:04.197
medicine a lot.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.265
But-- But who would do that?

06:05.265 --> 06:06.800
I don't-- Lots of people,

06:06.800 --> 06:07.468
evidently.

06:07.468 --> 06:08.135
Nope.

06:08.135 --> 06:10.738
It was one weirdo in 1982.

06:10.738 --> 06:11.405
(snaps fingers)

06:11.405 --> 06:12.072
Here are your Bennies.

06:12.072 --> 06:12.973
Oh, this is too far back.

06:12.973 --> 06:13.941
This is the '50s, whoops.

06:13.941 --> 06:14.608
(snaps fingers)

06:14.608 --> 06:15.275
Here are you Quaaludes.

06:15.275 --> 06:16.410
Ah, '80s, here we are.

06:16.410 --> 06:17.377
What the hell?

06:17.377 --> 06:19.379
In 1982, seven people were

06:19.379 --> 06:21.048
killed from cyanide placed

06:21.048 --> 06:22.650
inside of Tylenol bottles.

06:22.650 --> 06:23.884
We don't know who did it and we

06:23.884 --> 06:25.586
don't know why they did it, but

06:25.586 --> 06:27.555
let's make the educated guess

06:27.555 --> 06:29.156
that it was a crazy person.

06:29.156 --> 06:30.991
I'm doing this for no reason!

06:30.991 --> 06:33.427
I make no sense!

06:33.427 --> 06:34.227
There were also a few

06:34.227 --> 06:36.263
copycats, which, that's kind of

06:36.263 --> 06:37.397
a weird phrase, isn't it, come

06:37.397 --> 06:38.065
to think of it?

06:38.065 --> 06:39.567
Like, who's ever seen a cat copy

06:39.567 --> 06:40.233
another cat?

06:40.233 --> 06:41.134
Hey, can we focus, please?

06:41.134 --> 06:44.004
There is a murderer with no

06:44.004 --> 06:45.405
motive, like, one aisle--

06:45.405 --> 06:46.674
That's terrifying.

06:46.674 --> 06:47.808
Yeah, it is.

06:47.808 --> 06:49.443
And that's why the world went

06:49.443 --> 06:51.612
nuts over this story, which left

06:51.612 --> 06:53.246
Tylenol with a wee bit of

06:53.246 --> 06:55.115
a PR problem.

06:55.115 --> 06:56.750
Gentlemen, and one tough lady

06:56.750 --> 06:57.585
who we don't respect because

06:57.585 --> 06:59.086
it's the early '80s, what do

06:59.086 --> 06:59.753
we do?

06:59.753 --> 07:00.921
Make people feel safe, sir.

07:00.921 --> 07:02.122
Make people feel safe, sir.

07:02.122 --> 07:03.290
Great idea, Brian.

07:03.290 --> 07:04.692
I love your male brain.

07:04.692 --> 07:07.160
Let us make people feel safe!

07:07.160 --> 07:08.428
And that's what they did.

07:08.428 --> 07:09.763
They yanked Tylenol off the

07:09.763 --> 07:11.164
shelves and a few months later

07:11.164 --> 07:12.099
introduced the world to the

07:12.099 --> 07:14.001
first tamper-resistant seal.

07:14.001 --> 07:15.335
The public was reassured,

07:15.335 --> 07:16.637
Tylenol sales completely

07:16.637 --> 07:18.038
rebounded, and every other

07:18.038 --> 07:19.673
medicine soon did the same.

07:19.673 --> 07:20.608
Phil?

07:20.608 --> 07:21.975
Phil?

07:21.975 --> 07:23.176
Phil?

07:23.176 --> 07:23.977
Hey!

07:23.977 --> 07:24.978
But the tamper-resistant

07:24.978 --> 07:27.147
seal is just more security

07:27.147 --> 07:27.815
theater.

07:27.815 --> 07:28.482
It is?

07:28.482 --> 07:29.149
Yeah.

07:29.149 --> 07:30.984
It may make you feel safer, but

07:30.984 --> 07:32.720
it doesn't actually protect you

07:32.720 --> 07:33.787
from murderers.

07:33.787 --> 07:34.454
Think about it.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.123
If a real whackadoo really

07:36.123 --> 07:37.357
wanted to hurt you, you think a

07:37.357 --> 07:38.859
little piece of plastic is gonna

07:38.859 --> 07:39.693
stop him?

07:39.693 --> 07:41.529
Hey, that's true!

07:41.529 --> 07:43.163
I could-- I could poke a syringe

07:43.163 --> 07:45.332
through the seal, or put contact

07:45.332 --> 07:46.466
poison on the outside of the

07:46.466 --> 07:49.302
bottle, or what if I broke into

07:49.302 --> 07:50.337
the factory?

07:50.337 --> 07:51.171
Stop!

07:51.171 --> 07:52.139
And why limit yourself

07:52.139 --> 07:53.073
to Tylenol?

07:53.073 --> 07:54.041
You could hurt people any number

07:54.041 --> 07:54.875
of ways.

07:54.875 --> 07:56.309
Yeah, yeah, like I could put

07:56.309 --> 07:58.078
rat poison in a salad bar.

07:58.078 --> 07:59.079
I could hide barbed wire

07:59.079 --> 07:59.813
in a sandbox.

07:59.813 --> 08:00.581
Oh, yeah, or-- I'm just

08:00.581 --> 08:01.649
spitballing here-- what if you

08:01.649 --> 08:03.684
put arsenic in a Super Soaker?

08:03.684 --> 08:04.351
Yeah.

08:04.351 --> 08:05.719
Ooh, okay, hi.

08:05.719 --> 08:07.420
I'm a lawyer from the network.

08:07.420 --> 08:08.589
We'd prefer if you didn't give

08:08.589 --> 08:10.223
crazy people ideas for how to

08:10.223 --> 08:12.359
kill, on the air.

08:12.359 --> 08:13.260
Fair point.

08:13.260 --> 08:14.662
Luckily, serial killers

08:14.662 --> 08:15.328
are rare.

08:15.328 --> 08:16.363
You don't really need to worry

08:16.363 --> 08:17.030
about them.

08:17.030 --> 08:17.931
Yeah, but he killed seven

08:17.931 --> 08:18.599
people.

08:18.599 --> 08:19.266
That's a lot.

08:19.266 --> 08:19.933
That's, like, all the

08:19.933 --> 08:20.768
Kardashians.

08:20.768 --> 08:21.935
Or half the Duggars.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.503
But while we were focused on one

08:23.503 --> 08:25.205
fluke incident, we ignored the

08:25.205 --> 08:27.741
hard truth that 150 people die

08:27.741 --> 08:29.442
every year from what's in these

08:29.442 --> 08:30.177
bottles.

08:30.177 --> 08:31.344
Asbestos?

08:31.344 --> 08:32.079
BPAs?

08:32.079 --> 08:33.346
(gasps) Little bugs?

08:33.346 --> 08:35.415
No, the pills.

08:35.415 --> 08:36.684
The pills, that's crazy.

08:36.684 --> 08:37.350
I know.

08:37.350 --> 08:38.919
Because for years, Tylenol was

08:38.919 --> 08:40.420
advertised as if it were one of

08:40.420 --> 08:42.189
the safest drugs on the market.

